<br>
1.  Get an orb of infinite void.  Takes a couple of groups now but not too bad.  AC 35 +5wis/int 75hp/mana.  Blows away your shield.  <br>
<br>
2.  Change your Othmir Prexus Totem into an Idol of the Thorned.  Idol gives +ac, +sta and +hp.  Sure, its a downgrade, but you can always throw on your totem again when you put on your resist gear.<br>
<br>
3.  Your wrists have low AC.  You can get a Coldain Military Bracer or some Vellious Quest Armor to improve that.<br>
<br>
4.  Your belt is another way to get mana/hp.  The oakleaf girdle is 40mana/hp, the bone clasped girdle is 75mana/hp and you can get the uber ones too - grotesque girdle, brell girdle or belt of dwarf slaying :)<br>
<br>
5.  Your arms are only Ac7 - several good arms out there.  Personally I recommend Gladiator Chain Arms or Azure Sleeves.<br>
<br>
6.  Another option you have is to wear a fungi tunic.  That will raise some ac and make you lazy as you won't have to cast regrowth.  <br>
<br>
7.  The gloves to Slime Blood of Cazic Thule if you can find a pair.  AC 16 +2 to all stats.  Slight AC upgrade.<br>
<br>
You are on the cusp of being needing really uber gear.  Improving from what you have is tough but it can be done.<br>
